President Obama will be hosting the North American Leaders' Summit in Honolulu, Hawaii on November 13, 2011. The summit will involve Prime Minister Stephen Harper of Canada and President Felipe Calderon of Mexico. The meeting will focus on various areas of cooperation such as competitiveness, citizen security, energy and climate change, and North America's role in global economic, political, and security issues. The previous summit was held in Guadalajara in August 2009.